article.headline: Pennsylvania 79, Cornell 52
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Tim Bagley and Ibrahim Jaaber scored 17 points apiece and Jeff Schiffner added 13 as Penn defeated Cornell 79-52 in Ivy League play on Saturday. Cornell (10-11, 5-3 Ivy) never held a lead. The Big Red trailed 26-18 with 7:33 left in the first half before the Quakers went on a 26-2 run to push their lead to 32 points. Penn (12-8, 5-2 Ivy) shot 50-9 percent from the field including 9-for-17 from 3-point range. Cornell shot 37.7 percent from the field. Jaaber had a career-high 17 points, 11 in the first half. Ka'Ron Barnes scored 17 of his 22 points for Cornell in the second half, but didn't receive enough support to mount a significant run. Lenny Collins added 9 points for Cornell. Cody Toppert, who came into the game averaging 17.2 points per game, was held to 7 points.
